Here are the **consolidated design specifications** for the **`TimelinePage`** in Zoomout, based on your locked-in ASCII visualization and system architecture:

---

## 🔧 1. **Layout**

A vertically stacked, horizontally scrollable interface structured into the following main blocks:

* **Header / Title Block**: Zoomout identity and page title
* **Top Controls Bar**: Search, filters, zoom
* **Legend**: Color-coded categories
* **Contradiction Summary**: Box showing active contradiction’s meaning
* **Timeline Canvas**: Scrollable canvas of rows, one per contradiction timeline
* **Timeline Zoom & Scroll Controls**
* **Slide-in Panels** (conditionally rendered): Phase, Event, Timeline detail
* **Footer**

---

## 🎯 2. **Visual Hierarchy & Design Considerations**

| Element                | Role                         | Priority    | Style Notes                     |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------------- | ----------- | ------------------------------- |
| Page Title             | Branding + orientation       | High        | Bold, left-aligned              |
| Filters Bar            | User control interface       | High        | Subtle borders, intuitive icons |
| Contradiction Summary  | Anchoring frame of reference | Medium-High | Italic, muted background        |
| Timeline Rows          | Core visual element          | Highest     | Equal height rows, color-coded  |
| Event Dots             | Navigation + exploration     | High        | Hover effects, tooltips         |
| Panels                 | Deep info layers             | On-demand   | Slide-in, z-index overlay       |
| Zoom & Scroll Controls | Utility navigation           | Medium      | Fixed positioning               |
| Footer                 | Low context                  | Low         | Minimal style                   |

---

## 🧩 3. **Component Breakdown**

```
<TimelinePage>
├── <FiltersAndControls>
│   ├── <SearchBar />
│   ├── <CategoryFilter />
│   ├── <ContradictionFilter />
│   └── <ZoomSelector />
├── <LegendBar>
│   └── <LegendItem /> × n
├── <CoreContradictionSummary />
├── <TimelineCanvas>
│   └── <TimelineRow> × 7
│       ├── <TimelineLabel />
│       └── <TimelineTrack>
│           ├── <PhaseBlock /> × n
│           └── <EventDot /> × n
├── <ZoomSlider />
├── <TimelineScrollbar />
├── <PhaseDetailPanel /> (conditional)
├── <EventDetailPanel /> (conditional)
├── <SelectedTimelineDetailsPanel /> (conditional)
└── <Footer />
```

---

## 🔄 4. **Component Behavior**

| Component                               | Behavior                                             |
| --------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `SearchBar`                             | Filters timelines by title/keywords                  |
| `CategoryFilter`, `ContradictionFilter` | Updates visible rows                                 |
| `ZoomSelector`                          | Changes timeline granularity (Year ⇄ Decade ⇄ Phase) |
| `TimelineTrack`                         | Scrollable horizontally, shows phases and events     |
| `PhaseBlock`                            | On click → opens `<PhaseDetailPanel>`                |
| `EventDot`                              | On click → opens `<EventDetailPanel>`                |
| `SelectedTimelineDetailsPanel`          | Opens on explicit timeline click or zoom-in          |
| `ZoomSlider`                            | Adjusts time axis scale                              |
| `TimelineScrollbar`                     | Scrolls all `<TimelineTrack>` in sync                |
| `LegendItem`                            | Static, color reference                              |

---

## 🔁 5. **Interaction Flows**

1. **Search / Filter / Zoom**

   * User uses top bar → triggers filtering in `<TimelineCanvas>`
   * Zoom level alters phase granularity (updates `<PhaseBlock>` rendering logic)

2. **Scroll Navigation**

   * Horizontal scroll bar affects all tracks
   * Zoom slider also scales time axis across all rows

3. **Clicking PhaseBlock**

   * Loads `<PhaseDetailPanel>` with summary, events, structures, struggles

4. **Clicking EventDot**

   * Loads `<EventDetailPanel>` with full metadata, links, motion, scale, etc.

5. **Clicking Timeline Label**

   * Opens `<SelectedTimelineDetailsPanel>` for macro view

---

## 🧠 6. **Key UI Behavior**

| Feature             | Behavior                                          |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| Sticky Top Bar      | Top filters + zoom remain on top as user scrolls  |
| Synchronized Scroll | All timeline rows scroll together horizontally    |
| Conditional Panels  | Slide-in on trigger, stacked z-index              |
| Responsive Grid     | Rows collapse into accordion layout on mobile     |
| Tooltip on Hover    | EventDot shows headline & year                    |
| Color-coded Phases  | Indicates status: active/closed/high rupture etc. |

---

## 🎨 7. **Visual Design Guidelines**

| Design Token        | Value                                |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Primary Font        | Inter / Roboto (Sans-serif)          |
| Timeline Row Height | 80–100px                             |
| EventDot Size       | 8–12px, circular, hover-scale: 1.25x |
| PhaseBlock Colors   | Per status (theme-light compatible)  |
| Background          | #F8F9FA (light), #212529 (dark)      |
| Panel BG            | White (light) / #1E1E1E (dark)       |
| Accent Color        | #FF6B6B (calls to action)            |
| Border Radius       | 6px (cards, buttons, panels)         |
| Padding             | 16px standard grid                   |
| Icon Set            | Tabler Icons or Bootstrap Icons      |

---

